5-07-09 00:00:00','Arce-Bailon-Arce Architects',1,'2015-06-05 00:00:00','2015-06-17 00:00:00',8500000.00,8489593.00,NULL,'','2015-06-26 00:00:00','2015-08-31 00:00:00','2015-06-23 00:00:00',NULL,'2015-06-22 07:38:11','2015-08-24 00:20:57','','','The required Professional Services’ scope of work for the UPOU ICC shall be submitted to the UPOU within the following time per phase:\r\nPhase 1  – shall not exceed ten (10) calendar days 	upon the commencement of the Consultant’s services\r\nPhase 2  – shall not exceed fifteen (15) calendar days upon the approval of Phase 1\r\nPhase 3  – shall not exceed ten (10) calendar days upon the approval of Phase 2\r\nPhase 4  – shall not exceed thirty-five (35) calendar days upon the approval of Phase 3\r\n*Total is 70 calendar days\r\n*The time of review and approval by the UP Open University of different works shall not be included in the period of work of the Consultant.\r\n','',70,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(94,360,'Design Services','','','*Pre-design services already submitted and approved by the Chancellor.\r\n*Pending approval of the submitted indicative master planning services which includes preliminary cost estimate. Consultant was advised to do value engineering.\r\n*The consultant submitted revised indicative master planning services on July 22, 2015. Pending approval by the TWG and the Chancellor.\r\n*Comments and suggestions for the revised indicative master planning services were forwarded to A.C. Ong last July 31, 2015. Pending submission of the revised design from A.C. Ong.\r\n*As of August 19, 2015, no movement on the design phase. UPOU\'s Assistant to the Vice Chancellor for Finance and Administration, Prof. Luna will follow-up A.C. Ong regarding their next submission.\r\n*A meeting regarding AC Ong\'s submissions was held last Sept. 11, 2015. They have been given a deadline on Sept. 29, 2015 to submit the complete detailed architectural and engineering design and the bidding documents on or before Sept. 29, 2015.\r\n*A.C. Ong emailed a copy of the technical specifications of the design.\r\n*As of Sept. 30, 2015 morning, no submission of the final design output from A.C. Ong was received.\r\n*Complete sets of plans, specifications, and Bill of Quantities was submitted by A.C. Ong on the afternoon of Sept. 30, 2015. For review of UPOU engineers and TWG.',75.00,'2015-09-11 00:00:00','A.C. Ong Consulting Services',1,'2015-03-27 00:00:00','2015-04-24 00:00:00',1050000.00,1049424.21,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2015-04-24 00:00:00',NULL,'2015-07-07 02:28:12','2015-10-02 00:46:58','','','','The three faculties of study of UPOU - FMDS, FICS, FEd.',43,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(95,358,'Provision of Solar Power System in UPOU Community Hub Building','The provision of a Solar Photovoltaic (PV) system in the UPOU Community Hub building is in line with the UP System’s goal of promoting the use of green technology through all its constituent universities. The solar PV system shall be a grid-tied system to be connected to the MERALCO’s grid. Several electrical loads in the building shall be using the electricity harnessed by the system while the excess electricity generated by the system shall be supplied to the grid and the equivalent amount of this electricity shall be deducted to the electric bill of the UPOU. The usage of this green technology is intended to help UPOU in its drive for increased energy efficiency.','','*Financial proposal of the bidder with the highest rating in technical proposal opened on 26 May 2015.\r\n*Materials to be used for approval as of June 30, 2015.\r\n*Pre-construction meeting held July 10, 2015. It was agreed that the contract time would be temporarily suspended until the full turn-over of the Community Hub on July 21, 2015.\r\n*RC De Villa submitted request for time suspension dated July 14, 2015\r\n*Contract time resumed on July 27, 2015\r\n*RC De Villa submitted a letter stating that they are just waiting for the delivery of the materials after which installation shall follow.\r\n*Upon delivery of the materials on Sept. 09, 2015, the contractor then started project on Sept. 10, 2015. Projected completion of the installation of the materials is on Sept. 14, 2015.\r\n*A temporary power interruption was conducted on Sept. 14, 2015 to connect the Solar PV System to the electrical system of the UPOU Community Hub Building. Testing and commissioning of the system is scheduled on Sept. 15, 2015.\r\n*As of Sept. 21, 2015, the project was already 100% completed. The net-metering application was deducted to the contractor\'s scope of work as it would take 5-6 months to process with Meralco.',100.00,'2015-09-21 00:00:00','RC De Villa Construction & Development Corporation',1,'2015-06-05 00:00:00','2015-07-08 00:00:00',2910675.72,2356221.55,2384714.13,'',NULL,'2015-10-25 00:00:00','2015-07-27 00:00:00','2015-09-21 00:00:00','2015-07-13 02:16:16','2015-09-23 07:56:57','','','','UPOU Community Hub occupants (Info office)',90,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(96,358,'Rain Harvesting for the UPOU Community Hub Building','The University of the Philippines Open University is committed to promote in its drive to set an example for environmentally and economically sustainable projects. One of these projects is its UPOU Community Hub building which is now nearing completion. This project has been designed to feature green architecture and other green technologies. The rain harvesting component for the UPOU Community Hub building which will use the roof & gutters as collectors is intended to help conserve water by providing an additional supply of water that will be used in flushing urinals and water closets. The operation and maintenance of the rain harvesting facility will be simple and will only require part time trained maintenance personnel.','','*The project is on the proposal stage.\r\n*The pre-procurement conference of the project is scheduled to be on Sept. 10, 2015.\r\n*The project 