t and increased research productivity','Budget earmarked on 07 Jan 2014',0.00,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,10000000.00,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-06-12 05:59:33','2015-08-27 01:19:08',1,5,NULL,'','','',0,0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,5,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(13,'Extension of Kolehiyo ng Agham Building','IUPB2015-013','','','',0.00,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,5940000.00,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-06-12 05:59:33','2015-08-27 01:19:29',1,5,NULL,'','','',0,0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,5,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(14,'Demolition of Old Psychology Building to Additional Rooms','IUPB2015-014','','','',0.00,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,2475000.00,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-06-12 05:59:33','2015-08-27 01:20:25',1,5,NULL,'','','',0,0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(15,'Construction of the UPPS-Cebu SRP Building & Auditorium','IUPC2015-001','Construction of a new building for the UP Professional Schools at Cebu SRP, to offer graduate programs in business administration, IT and related fields','Enhanced learning environment','Completed as of Dec 2012.\r\n\r\nRenovation  to add control room and waiting area to the Auditorium and lower the existing stage.',100.00,NULL,'C.E. Padilla Construction, Inc.',1,'2011-11-08 00:00:00','2011-11-24 00:00:00',63000000.00,62586819.25,62883195.72,'','2011-11-25 00:00:00','2012-12-21 00:00:00','2011-12-05 00:00:00','2015-05-15 00:00:00','2015-06-12 05:59:33','2015-09-14 02:46:25',2,1,'2012-12-15 00:00:00','Renovation and Addition Works Planned:  (1) Demolish the existing stage in the Auditorium and lower it to 0.60 cm finish level from the current 1.00m height, (2) Add a Control Room and Waiting Room at the front of the Auditorium.  Drawings and specifications are complete.  ABC is P1.2 Million','','There were problems remaining with the LAN after the December 2012 completion date and the problems were solved only in 2015.  The contractor, CE Padilla Construction Inc., had the LAN subcontracted but the work was done by electricians and not by computer network specialists, which led to problems, such as the lack of \"as-built\" plans.\r\n\r\nA Pre-Bid Conference for the Renovation of the Auditorium was held on August 12 attended by three contractors.',0,0,'',NULL,875,296376.47,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(16,'Modernization of UP Cebu Science Lab & Expansion of Computer Lab Equipment','IUPC2015-002','Modernization of UP Cebu Science Lab & Expansion of Computer Lab Equipment','Enhanced learning/research environment and increased research productivity','Ongoing\r\n Status updated as of 11 May 2015\r\n\r\nCompleted.  All items were delivered as of April 29, 2015.\r\n\r\nCompleted.  No further updates needed.',100.00,NULL,'Fotoline Express Inc.,  Catron Computer Technology, Asian Home Appliance Center Co. Inc.,  CITI Appliance MC Corp., New Datche Phils Traders Corp, RCP Manufacturing Co.  Inc., DJ PCWise Corp, Cebu Progress Commercial, TFE Sales & Marketing Corp, Harmanson Electronic Center, Vican Marketing, Asian Pacific Computer Sales, iShop Computer Service Inc., Cebu AI Logic Inc., Exclusive Traders Inc.,  Yana Chemodities,  Scientific Product Company, Harnwell Chemicals, Sciencestar Corp, Cebu Bionic Builders Supply Inc., Shurebright Electrical Supplies, Guilbern Corporation, Labtrade Scientific Trade Center, Philab Industries, Ng Khai Development Corp, Xcomp Computer Sales & Services Inc., Biometrix System and Trading Corp, World Digital Corp, Silicon Valley, Unilab, Perfect Star PC Shop, 7Core Communications Inc.',NULL,NULL,NULL,12870000.00,12179653.00,12809297.09,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-06-12 05:59:33','2015-09-21 04:12:57',2,1,'2015-04-19 00:00:00','Just look at the number of contractors involved - I really, really, really need help on this! \r\n\r\nNo help yet. :(','','Completed as of April 29, 2015\r\n\r\nNo updates as of August 17, 2015.  Project completed.',0,0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,9,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(17,'Design & Construction of the UP Cebu Library at Lahug','IUPC2015-003','Design & Construction of the UP Cebu Library at Lahug','Enhanced learning/research environment and increased research productivity','Completed as of 08 May 2015\r\n\r\nNo wi-fi connectivity while the UP Cebu CSU tries to reconfigure the wi-fi system for the whole campus.\r\n\r\nCeiling on lobby at the second floor will be rectified from the period September 14 - 19, 2015',100.00,NULL,'Rex E. Morales Construction',3,'2013-05-14 00:00:00','2013-11-25 00:00:00',25245000.00,23311818.86,NULL,'','2013-11-27 00:00:00','2014-11-26 00:00:00',NULL,'2015-05-08 00:00:00','2015-06-12 05:59:33','2015-10-09 06:01:01',2,1,'2015-05-08 00:00:00','There was a Partial Turn-Over on June 22, 2015 with the contractor submitting a Letter of Undertaking promising to complete the punchlist and submit the Occupancy Permit by July 31, 2015.  Library personnel have been moving  books and equipment into the retrofitted building since the partial turn-over.  The Performance Arts Hall on the Second Floor was used for a program on June 24, 2014. \r\n\r\nRectification of Punchlist on-going.\r\n\r\nContractor has not yet submitted Occupancy Permit as of August 11, 2015\r\n\r\nAs of August 17, 2015 is already being used by students and LAN is working.  However, not all wi-fi access points have been installed and those installed by CSU have limitations.','BAC Chair said that variation orders will actually be regarded as extra work.   UP Cebu still waiting for financial support from System.','Original contract deadline was on November 26, 2014 but was extended by two months.\r\n\r\nOn-going rectification works:  painting of second floor lobby ceiling, retouching of columns at entrance canopy.\r\n\r\nRectification of painting of exterior columns done.\r\n\r\nThere was leak at the Male Toilet on the second floor which  resulted in dampness of the carpet tiles in the adjoining AVR and dripping in the library on the ground floor.  Contractor send their plumber and the leak was fixed during the weekend.',0,1,'UP Cebu Library',365,60,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(18,'Design & Construction of the UP Cebu Library at SRP','IUPC2015-004','Design & Construction of the UP Cebu Library at SRP','Enhanced learning/research environment and increased research productivity','Ongoing',68.20,'2015-09-26 00:00:00','C.E. Padilla Construction Incorporated',1,'2013-06-18 00:00:00','2013-09-11 00:00:00',72765000.00,72698978.88,NULL,'','2013-09-16 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-06-12 05:59:33','2015-10-09 06:06:32',2,2,NULL,'','','Project is delayed.  Last approved time extension was July 6, 2015 but the contractor is requesting for additional 120 days due to Variation Order No. 1.   Contractor was given 90 days extension for Variation  Order No. 1 and 15 days extension time for  Variation Order No. 2.\r\n\r\nEvaluation given by OCA for Variation Orders 1 & 2 were contested by the Contractor.  Campus Architect recommended to the Dean that the Oblation Statue, which was the subject of Variation Order no. 2, be taken out from the main scope of works so that the contractor will not use it as another reason to ask for a time extension.\r\n\r\nContractor met with the Dean and Campus Architect last September 2, 2015.  A new time extension - the final one - has been set on December 15, 2015.',1,0,'UP Cebu Library\r\nTBI',365,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(19,'UP Cebu High School Building','IUPC2015-005','Construction of a new building for the UP Cebu High School','Enhanced learning environment','NTP has been issued; work cannot proceed because the area needs to be cleared of informal settlers.  \r\n\r\nInformal settlers still there.',0.00,NULL,'A. A. Masong Construction',3,'2013-09-20 00:00:00','2014-03-17 00:00:00',60000000.00,54335583.99,NULL,'2013 CO Budget',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-06-12 05:59:33','2015-09-29 07:06:24',2,3,NULL,'Contractor has completed the A&E Design phase.  Building permits not applied for as per advice of the UP Cebu legal office since building permit is valid for only one year and there is  no indication that the informal settlers will relocate or be relocated within that period.\r\n\r\nNo movement.','','Informal settlers are still present at the site and UP Cebu has met with them regarding relocation to a site offered by the Cebu Provincial Capitol.\r\n\r\nMeeting with informal settlers at the barangay hall last July 10 yielded no clear-cut results.  Another meeting will be scheduled by the barangay captain.',0,1,'UP High School Department',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(20,'Design & Construction of Arts & Sciences Building Extension','IUPC2015-006','Design & Construction of Arts & Sciences Building Extension','Enhanced learning environment','NOA issued on 20 Jan 2015\r\nNTP issued on 23 Feb 2015\r\nDesign phase complete\r\nContractor now applying for Locational Clearance from the city zoning department\r\nStatus updated as of 11 May 2015',26.67,NULL,'Maqueserg Construction and General Merchandise\r\n\r\nContractor will start construction even without a building permit once they receive the mobilization fee (15% of contract cost).\r\n\r\nContractor has been informed that their mobilization fee will be released within the next few days.  Mobilization for this project may start within the week.',2,'2015-01-20 00:00:00','2015-02-23 00:00:00',13000000.00,12995698.05,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-06-12 05:59:33','2015-10-09 06:15:38',2,2,NULL,'The contractor is processing the new set of drawings but the construction will be on hold until such time that the informal settlers will give way to an access road to make the site more accessible to heavy equipment.\r\n\r\nInformal settlers block access from the main road.  Contractor will start work once they will have an application number from the Office of the Building Official.\r\n\r\nLocational Clearance not yet issued as of August 11, 2015\r\n\r\nMaqueserg Construction has received mobilization fee.  Will be meeting with contractor within the  week so construction can start.','','Project location was changed since building the project at the original location would block the view of the existing Undergraduate Studies Building.  New location is at the side of the UGSB but is currently inaccessible to vehicles and construction equipment due to informal settlers.   Barangay Lahug has summoned the informal settlers and UP Cebu to a meeting on July 10, 2015 regarding the issue of transferring the IS.\r\n\r\nMeeting on July 10 with informal settlers did not yield any results except to agree to meet again.\r\n\r\nThere will be a public hearing on the special permit  for tree-cutting requested by UP Cebu  on October 7, Wednesday.\r\n\r\nThe contractor wants to use the existing  Fine Arts Workshop as part of their temporary facilities since there is very little available space at the site to store materials and house their workers.  In return, they will build the AH Department, which uses the workshop, another workshop in which to transfer their materials.  OCA designed a workshop for the AH Department near the clinic and it was just approved by the AH Faculty.',0,0,'Arts & Sciences Cluster',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(21,'Expansion of the Mini Gallery & Refurbishment of the UP Cebu Conference Hall & AVR into the UP Cebu Performing Arts Hall','IUPC2015-007','Expansion of the Mini Gallery & Refurbishment of the UP Cebu Conference Hall & AVR into the UP Cebu Performing Arts Hall','Improved access to academic support facilities and services for UP faculty, students & staff','NOA issued on 18 Dec 2014\r\nNTP issued on 23 Feb 2015\r\n\r\nContractor for the Performing Arts Hall is going through the punchlist and will submit their final billing within May 2015.\r\nStatus updated as of 11 May 2015\r\n\r\n',98.00,'2015-10-06 00:00:00','Maqueserg Construction and General Merchandise',1,'2014-12-18 00:00:00','2015-02-23 00:00:00',8400000.00,808632.82,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-06-12 05:59:33','2015-10-09 06:18:08',2,2,NULL,'Project suspended while contractor is sourcing materials not included in the BOQ - this will be covered in a variation order.\r\n\r\nEnd-users from AH Cluster have made walkthrough through Mini Gallery.\r\n\r\nRectification of the Performance Arts Hall lobby ceiling will be done from September 14 - 19, 2015.\r\nRectification works for the Mini Gallery is on-going. ','','Work has been temporarily halted as the contractor\'s representative on site met a vehicular accident.   Pending work involves installation of cove lighting, panelboards and circuit breakers.  Painting works is not yet final.\r\n\r\nPerformance Arts Hall has already been used for a program by UP Cebu on June 24, 2015, after partial turn-over by the contractor, Rex Morales Construction.  Lighting, sound system and sound insulation have been installed.  Curtain supplier has made final measurements for window and stage curtains.  UP Cebu Dean has instructed the Campus Engineer to make some changes to the rooms at the back of the hall, such transferring the control room and converting the current control room into a small conference room.\r\n\r\nThere will be a walkthrough  together with the end-users on August 5, 2015 at 9AM.\r\n\r\nCampus Architect and End-Users made a walkthrough and the Contractor was told about deficiences in the project.  He will commence rectification on August 10, 2015\r\n\r\nPerformance Arts Hall was used for a big meeting seating 500 persons.  AVR1 was used for a conference by UP Bagiuo chancellors last week.\r\n\r\nOn-going rectification works for Mini Gallery:  Repainting of Display Panels, additional dropped ceiling and electrical works.\r\n\r\nContractor rectified painting works as per punchlist.\r\n\r\nWork has been inspected and approved by the end-users.  Minor items will be done when the contractor starts with the AS Extension Building.  Contractor will be submitting his final billing.',0,0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,5,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(22,'Repair, Rehabilitation & Renovation of Various Classrooms, Labs & Offices','IUPC2015-008','Repair, Rehabilitation & Renovation of Various Classrooms, Labs & Offices\r\nParticulars:\r\n1) Expansion of AH Cluster Faculty Room: Php 1,500,000.00\r\n2) Expansion of Sciences Cluster Area for Sciences Cluster Head and Offices: Php 1,5000,000.00\r\n3) Renovation of A.S. Building rooms for safety in case of emergencies: P1,000,000.00\r\n4) Renovation of Psychology Laboratory: Php 500,000.00\r\n5) Repair of the BMC Building ceiling: Php 330,000.00\r\n6) Conversion of Unused Shower Room into a Thesis-Advising Room: Php 112,880.00\r\n7) Renovation of the Office of Student Affairs:  Php 500,000.00\r\n8) Renovation of CSU Data Center: Php 100,000.00\r\n9) Addition of Covered Walks and Pathways from Undergraduate Studies Building to Graduate Program Building 2: Php 497,120.00\r\n10) Renovation of TLRC Underground room: Php 150,000.00\r\n\r\nNote: Items 1 & 2 were lumped together under one project with an ABC of Php 3M \r\n            is yet to be bidded out.\r\n            Items 3 - 8 were lumped together under one project with 6 lots with a total \r\n            ABC of Php 2,542,880.00\r\n            Items 9 & 10 have not been bidded out yet.','Enhanced learning/research environment and increased research productivity','For Purchase Request/JO preparation.\r\n\r\nBid documents are ready.\r\n\r\nPost qualification of BT Construction and General Services ongoing.',0.00,NULL,'Bidding for various renovations for 6 lots was won by BT Construction during opening of bids last August 25.  Post qualification will be done in a few days.  ',1,NULL,NULL,6190000.00,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-06-12 05:59:33','2015-09-21 04:27:41',2,6,NULL,'Pre-bid conference was held on August 12, 2015 with three contractors attending.  None of the contractors bought the bid documents before the conference.\r\n\r\nBAC Chair and TWG visited projects done by BT Construction & General Services as part of Post Qualification for this project.  Contract has not yet received the NOA for these projects.','','Pre-bid conference for items 3 - 8 was held on August 12, 2015.\r\n\r\nOpening of bids for items 3 - 8 was held on August 25, 2015.\r\n\r\nBidding for Items 1 & 2 - joined together as one project at Php3M -  will be done in September.',0,0,'Various end-users',NULL,NULL,NULL,3,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(23,'Construction of UP Cebu Guesthouse Building in UPD','IUPC2015-009','','','Pre-Bid Conference conducted on 02 Mar 2015\r\nBid Opening conducted on 16 Mar 2015\r\n\r\nDuring their visit to UP Cebu,  AVP Nestor Raneses and SPMO Head Isagani Bagus suggested that the bidding for the construction of the UPC Guesthouse in Diliman be conducted in UP Diliman.  To this end, UP Cebu is bidding out the design phase of this project but so far there has  been no takers.           ',2.00,NULL,'Two bidders participated in the A&E Design for the project:  New Adeson Construction Incorporated and K&K Builders with bids of P180,000 and P175,000, respectively.  OCA has  called the office of K&K Builders to get their feedback on the checklist faxed by SPMO.\r\n\r\nPost-qualification of K&K Builders, with the lowest bid of P175,000, is on-going.\r\n\r\nNotice of qualification was sent to K&K Builders last Friday, August 14, 2015.\r\n\r\nPO received by K & K Builders and they are currently working on A&E design of the project.  \r\n\r\nK & K Builders working on the architectural drawings for the Guesthouse. \r\n\r\nK & K Builders General Manager Arch. Jojo Opo said they will have the plumbing and electrical drawings by next week.',1,NULL,NULL,2600000.00,2615725.00,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-06-12 05:59:33','2015-10-09 06:19:19',2,6,NULL,'K&K Builders has been post qualified.','','',0,0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(24,'Construction of Classrooms-Existing UP Cebu High School','IUPC2015-010','','','Design by DPWH architect needed revision since it would cost more than P4.5M budget.    \r\n\r\nDesign by DPWH complete but will have to be re-estimated by the contractor.',1.00,NULL,'La Prueba Construction',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-06-12 05:59:33','2015-10-09 06:23:16',2,3,NULL,'There have been several changes to the design of this project.  The final design is for two classrooms, one on the ground floor and one on the  second floor, as well as comfort rooms.   The building will be located at the side of the Undergraduate Studies Building, behind the to-be-built A.S. Extension Building.\r\n\r\nThe DPWH informed UP Cebu that construction would start soon but that the University should shoulder the cost and responsibility of cutting down    trees.\r\n\r\nLocation of  building transferred to an area near the high school gym and the old library, part of which will be demolished.  Revised plans have been sent to the DPWH for production of construction drawings.  OCA is requesting for copy of the contractor\'s TOR and scope of works.\r\n\r\nHave not received any updates from the DPWH.','Government Agency - DPWH','Contractor,  La Prueba Construction, will commence work in a few weeks - according to the DPWH.\r\n\r\nUP Cebu will request DENR for permit to cut down trees at the location of the building. \r\n\r\nDPWH inspected the site again today, August 27.  Contractor is waiting for tree-cutting permit from DENR before construction can start.\r\n\r\nThere will be a public  hearing on October 14 in connection with UP Cebu\'s request for a special tree-cutting permit with the DENR.  Construction of the UP High School Classroom building will be one of the reasons for the tree-cutting.  If UP is unable to secure a tree-cutting permit,  the project location will have to moved to the old high school site, in which the Dean will have to write COA requesting for permission to demolish an old, unused high school building to give way to the new building.',0,0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(25,'Renovation of Existing UP High School Buildings','IUPC2015-011','Renovation, rehabilitation and repair of existing UP Cebu High School building','Enhanced learning environment','For final acceptance by End-user\r\n\r\nDPWH has issued a Certificate of Partial Turn-Over which  UP Cebu received on June 30, 2015.  As a pre-condition for signing the Partial Turn-Over,  Dean Liza Corro requested a Letter of Undertaking from District Engineer Nicomedes Leonor that all defects will be corrected before the final turn-over.  The turn-over was requested so that work which was not included in the Scope of Works of the contractor  -  such painting and tileworks -  could be undertaken by UP Cebu CDMO.   UP Cebu High School alumni have already pledged to donate in kind and cash to complete the project.\r\n\r\nLast August 28, the project was inspected by Rep. Ashley Acedillo, who funded the project, and DPWH officials led by District Engineer Nicomedes Leonor and his engineers and architects and the Contractor.  During the visit there was a heavy downpour and the water cascaded down inside the \"rehabilitated\" rooms much to the embarrasment of the DPWH officials present.  They vowed to change the roof and pledged to donate two air conditioning units to the high school department.  More than two weeks later nothing has been done.\r\n\r\nNo repairs done yet.',90.00,NULL,'La Prueba Construction',NULL,NULL,NULL,3000000.00,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-06-12 05:59:33','2015-10-09 06:24:05',2,2,NULL,'Terrible workmanship.\r\n\r\nUP Cebu will do the rectification work to make the project functional.  Rehabilitated buildings have no paint or new tiles.\r\n\r\nRehabilitated buildings were inaugurated last Friday, August 14, 2015.   UPHS Batch 1985 has promised to shoulder the cost of installing new tiles while UPHS Batch 1995 has promised to shoulder the cost of painting.\r\n\r\nElectrical work needs to be done.  End-user is writing the donor to complain about various defects in the building.\r\n\r\nLa Prueba has not yet done any rectification work as they had promised.','Government Agency - DPWH','La Prueba Construction received the Notice of Award (NOA) from DPWH on August 4, 2014.  Work has  been delayed and the UP Cebu Campus Engineer and Architect have pointed out defects in the contractor\'s workmanship and construction methodology.  Problems such as faulty electrical wiring, leaking roof and defective plastering have not been rectified.\r\n\r\nPartial Turn-Over waiting for signature from DPWH District Engineer Nicomedes Leonor before it comes into effect.\r\n\r\nDPWH District Engr. Nicomedes Leonor has signed the certificate of Partial Turn-Over.\r\n\r\nRepainting of the rooms completed.  No tiles yet.\r\n',0,0,'UP Cebu High School',NULL,NULL,NULL,3,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(27,'Marquee Room/Covered Gymnasium','IUPC2015-013','To provide a venue for sports activities and performancees and to provide UP Cebu with a source of i','','Design stage.\r\n\r\nNo movement as of August 11, 2015.\r\n\r\nAugust 17, 2015.  No movement on this project.  Studies sent by OCA received no feedback.\r\n\r\nThis project has been scrapped.',0.00,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,30000000.00,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-06-12 05:59:33','2015-08-27 13:23:53',2,4,NULL,'','','',0,0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(28,'Library/Learning Commons-Phase 2','IUPC2015-014','','','Proposal stage.\r\n\r\nProject as planned by ODPI cannot be implemented due to presence of informal settlers. \r\n\r\nProject not likely to be implemented as planned.  OCA is suggesting using the available space  -  i.e., space not occupied by informal settlers -  for Phase II of the Learning Commons.',0.00,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,30000000.00,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-06-12 05:59:33','2015-08-27 13:24:22',2,3,NULL,'','','',0,0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(29,'Construction of 2 storey BMC Building','IUPC2015-015','A 2-Storey concrete building with roof deck.  Ground floor will have 7.00m x 10.00m classrooms which can be divided into 4 smaller